### Expected behavior

When I want to insert an image into a bokeh icon and save it as an HTML file, I hope to get a bokeh icon containing the image

### Observed behavior

When I use the bokeh interface and want to insert an image into the bokeh icon, the image is imported, the source in the form of ColumnDataSource, source.data also has an array, the figure is created, and the image is put into it, and finally saved as HTML format, but the opened HTML file is blank, there is no bokeh icon, and no image
I exported source.data from pdb and combined it with gpt, but it still couldn't be solved. I think the problem is still in the combination of source and figure. I also tried adding RGBA conversion, but my image is jpg, which didn't help. I wrote it in Python on the server and need to save it as an HTML file and view the effect locally

